          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>What Is a Recurring Deposit?</h2></div>
            <p>A Recurring Deposit (RD) is a savings tool offered by banks and post offices that allows you to invest a fixed amount every month for a predetermined tenure, earning interest at FD-equivalent rates. At maturity, you receive the total of all deposits plus compounded interest — making it an excellent option for building a corpus through small, regular contributions.</p>
            <p>RDs are ideal for individuals who cannot invest a lump sum but want to save systematically. With monthly installments starting as low as ₹100 at post offices and ₹500 at most banks, anyone can start building wealth. The interest rate is fixed at the time of opening and remains unchanged throughout the tenure.</p>
            <p>RD interest is compounded quarterly, similar to fixed deposits. Tenures range from 6 months to 10 years at banks, while the Post Office RD has a fixed 5-year tenure. The discipline of mandatory monthly payments helps inculcate a strong savings habit while earning guaranteed returns.</p>
          </div>

